                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.5914/154</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-10-05T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 5, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>364. Parliamentary committee has reached a series of conclusions relative to its
                    course of procedure. It insists that the whole of the diplomatic correspondence
                    pertaining to the sale be submitted to it. When the material has been considered
                    by the committee the latter will decide upon what persons shall be called upon
                    to furnish information. At the meeting yesterday telegrams were despatched to
                    the West Indian colonial boards to the effect that the committee was desirous of
                    conferring with members of the boards. They must be selected in such a manner
                    that the prevailing views are represented. They are to arrive in Copenhagen
                    within the time limit set for the work of the committee. Governor Helweg Larsen
                    who has resigned is now in New York City. He is due here October 26th, also he
                    will be requested to furnish information. This procedure does away with the
                    demand of Socialist party for a referendum in the islands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
